# Per-edition release accounting.
#
# Certheim ships three stacked editions on three branches:
#     Community (base) -> Commercial -> Government
# Changes flow UP via bottom-up propagation MRs. To keep those MRs from choking
# on mechanical release files, each edition writes ONLY its own files:
#
#   editions/community.version     editions/community.changelog.md
#   editions/commercial.version    editions/commercial.changelog.md
#   editions/government.version    editions/government.changelog.md
#
# Because a higher edition never touches a lower edition's files (and only
# Community writes the root VERSION), a 3-way merge sees just one side change
# them -> they merge cleanly with NO conflict, no custom driver required.
#
# The `union` attributes below are belt-and-suspenders for the rare case two
# editions are merged with concurrent edits to the same accounting file: GitLab
# (Gitaly) honors the built-in `union` strategy server-side, so a merge keeps
# both sides' lines instead of raising a conflict.
editions/*.version        merge=union
editions/*.changelog.md   merge=union
CHANGELOG.md              merge=union

# NOTE on the build edition marker (backend/build_mode.py `EDITION = "..."`):
# it intentionally differs per branch and is NOT auto-merged here. A whole-file
# `merge=ours` would wrongly drop legitimate incoming changes to other lines, so
# if a Community change to build_mode.py ever conflicts on the EDITION line,
# resolve it by KEEPING THE TARGET BRANCH'S edition value (commercial stays
# "commercial", government stays "government"). See RELEASING.md.
